    "title" : "AuthHuaweiId.getAccessToken() has been deprecated",
    "body" : "<p><code>com.huawei.hms.support.feature.result.AbstractAuthAccount</code> <a href=\"https://developer.huawei.com/consumer/en/doc/hmscore-references/authaccount-0000001050315810#section525518587477\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>getAccessToken()</code></a> reads:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&gt; NOTICE<br/><br/>\nThe method has been deprecated.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>While I'm using <a href=\"https://id.huawei.com\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>HwIdAuthProvider</code></a> (<a href=\"https://developer.huawei.com/consumer/en/doc/hmscore-references/account-support-hwid-result-authhuaweiid-0000001050048492\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>AuthHuaweiId</code></a>), which depends on that access-token.</p>\n<pre><code>AGConnectAuthCredential credential = HwIdAuthProvider.credentialWithToken(token, true);\n</code></pre>\n<p><code>HuaweiIdAuthParams.setAccessToken()</code>, which requests returning the token along with the reponse, is also deprecated, therefore I'd assume the whole token-based flow is deprecated.</p>\n<p>What would be the recommend replacement for token-based Huawei ID?</p>\n<p>Actually, I use Huawei ID to connect <code>AGConnectAuth</code>.</p>\n",
